Jenna Etheridge, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Bloemfontein - The Supreme Court of Appeal (SCA) on Tuesday overturned a high court ruling that allowed a terminally ill cancer patient the right to commit suicide with a doctor&rsquo;s help.The High Court in Pretoria handed down the ruling in the case of Cape Town advocate Robin Stransham-Ford, 65, last year.It was appealed by the Minister of Justice and Correctional Services, the Minister of Health, the National Director of Public Prosecutions and the Health Professions Council of SA.This is a developing story. More to follow soon.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.